title: Puyallup police searching for suspect in interrupted burglary
text:
Police used a K-9 to search for a burglary suspect Thursday morning.
Puyallup police tweeted at 6:09 a.m. that a burglary was in progress at an occupied home when someone who lives there interrupted the intruder.
There was heavy police activity in the Crystal Ridge area while police conducted the search.
Police said they have no suspect description because the burglar fled before the homeowners saw them.
The suspect was not found.
Anyone who spots a suspicious person in the area is asked to call 911.
K9 track now complete in Crystal Ridge area. Suspect was not located. If you see suspicious activity or person this AM call 911.
